Mercury üß†üå©
As Mr. Mercury moves through the final degrees of Sagittarius we are being reminded to activate the right side of our brain, to understand certain things beyond logic and to see the ‚Äòbigger picture‚Äô. Mercury can be a cheeky planet - misconstruing information and perception - makes sense though, one person says something and the other might receive it in a completely different way - has a lot to do with where the natal mercury is in your chart. And understanding that we all have different ways of communicating. Mercury in Sag however is a cheeky fella - wanting to take you to the most expansive corners of the mind.. definitely potential for spiritual bypass here. Overlooking the details because ‚Äòlife is too short and, in the grand scheme of things, this moment is insignificant‚Äô says Sagittarius. However, for those of us that struggle to see beyond logic and reason, this transit helps us to navigate a more philosophical perspective. I say - make the most of this exciting, fun, cosmic joke mindset over the next few days. Allow your mind to take you on an adventure and speak your truth‚Ä¶ before Mercury enters Capricorn and we experience a sobering and disciplined state of mind. Remembering that the movement through the zodiac is a necessary cycle that we must all pass through - just like the cycle of nature & life - each archetype comes to teach us something and is part of the whole.
Art: @kamillacollages

Eclipse Musings ‚ú®
The dark moon has been upon us for the past 24 hours. Bringing with it the true flavour of death, darkness and osmosis. And as the Sun eclipses at 1:15 Perth/Bali time.. we are reborn into a fresh lunar cycle with the New Moon in Capricorn. 
Maybe you‚Äôve been exploring nostalgic moments, memories, music... old memories surfacing from the subconscious - and it is okay! Go into them. Explore them. But only with the intention of recognising how far you‚Äôve already come. The space between then and now. Understanding that although the body might have a conditioned trauma response to the past - that doesn‚Äôt have to be the reality of your present. You are okay. You are safe. You are home. Rewire these connections to the past. Allow what needs to surface to arise - so that when the eclipse occurs and the suns protective layer around the earth energetically thins.. we are able to consciously release and let go of that which no longer serves us. 
Then, heralding in the powerful energy of the new moon and expansive Jupiter, delicately choose how you may rebuild & start anew. What will these new foundations look, smell, feel and taste like? How can you be your own authority and set your own standards/rules. And a message to myself but reflection for you - how can you be the best person you can be in this and every moment? And fuck what everybody else thinks... üôÉ
Photography: @cloudatlase

This Eclipse will manifest for everybody differently. Some will barely feels it.. whereas others might feel it a lot! It all depends where 4 degrees of Capricorn lands in your birth chart and if this degree is aspecting anything else in your chart. For example - it is likely you‚Äôll feel this eclipse more if you have dominant placements in any of the cardinal signs (Aries, Cancer, Libra & Capricorn). Art by the wonderful @mr.babies üíì

Sun Trine Uranus üß†
Freeeedooom (Braveheart?)‚Ä¶ anyways, that is exactly what this dandy trine is shouting off of the rooftops. Freedom of self expression and creativity. Supporting us to radically transform our core selves and ego identity. Ego isn‚Äôt bad - it‚Äôs actually important that we all learn how to develop a healthy ego. And this transit can help us to do that in a grounded and stable way. Well.. as stable as Uranus can be! Uranus brings electric ‚Äòshock‚Äô energy with him - and he is kindly sending that energy to support the evolution of our Sun who is currently in Capricorn. Earth dominant beings - surrender to the shake up, invite a bit more spontaneity into your lives, let go of control and things needing to be one way. Uranus is going to show you brand new ways of being, doing and seeing. Shaking up the old paradigm. When we keep ourselves locked into a mould we are shutting ourselves off from receiving even bigger and better downloads/opportunities. How can you relinquish control today? If you do not surrender to & work with this transit - it is likely you‚Äôll be nervous, uptight, highly strung and things won‚Äôt be going ‚Äòyour‚Äô (conditioned/routined) way. A little nudge to step out of the norm and mundane. Without surprises life can get boring anyways! Thanks Uranus, we love you x

Venus square Uranus üå∑
Venus in Aquarius is square to Aquarius‚Äôs ruling planet of Uranus which is currently in Taurus whom is ruled by Venus (sorry if that confuses you). What we have here is a mutual reception. Two parents (planets) are ruling each others children. A square can indicate some tension, which is important because when things are easy breezy they don‚Äôt force us to change and grow. Erratic, unpredictable surprises and happenings in the realm of love and money are being served up today. Maybe you find out some shocking news, suddenly receive unexpected $ or enter into/end a relationship. This combo shakes the stability of a situation to it‚Äôs core - whether it appears as a good or bad experience. Uranus pushes us to evolve by shocking us awake. This square supports us in transforming our self-worth and what we‚Äôve been externally attaching ourselves to. Also supporting how we see beauty in the world and what the value of money means to us. Taking Venus in Aquarius‚Äôs lessons to a deeper level. Venus in Aquarius brought these themes into our psyche and now this square to Uranus brings them into reality. At the end of the day, everything is energy. Where are you directing your energy? And how is it being reflected back to you? Don‚Äôt get too comfortable over the next couple of days. See unpredictable events as an exciting opportunity to align closer with your path. It‚Äôs also priming us for the upcoming eclipse. 
Art by @35mmdeluz üå∏

Sun enters Capricorn ‚ôëÔ∏è Happy solar return Capricorn babes. The sun moves into Capricorn - the archetype of the elder, authority, structure, form and tradition. The archetype of building a strong foundation - driven by ambition and towards success. Whatever that means to you? I am excited as we reach this time of year and families gather. Capricorn is the pillar of the community. The space holder. The one that shares guidance, tough love and constructive criticism. Capricorn, ruled by Saturn, doesn‚Äôt allow itself to get away with much - they tend to be way too hard on themselves. But this is the most fitting energy to be working with leading up to the New Year. As you are blatantly reminded that you are the only one who is in-charge of your own reality. You are the only one that can take responsibility for your shortcomings and make a change. You are the only one that can put the hard work in to actually reap the rewards. With Capricorn there is no cutting corners and walking on egg shells. There is realism and confrontation - so you can become a stronger human that lives out of integrity. Capricorn calls us into maturity and adulthood. These folk need to be reminded how to evoke their inner child at times. But for the rest of us that need to get our shit together - call on your Cap or Virgo friends. And be prepared to get triggered! We only want to help. And Cap! Enjoy the view rather than constantly looking for the next mountain to climb. This is a beautiful opportunity to support each others endeavours and take a moment to acknowledge how far we have all come. Be a reflection of stability and centredness that your friends/family need - not to enable others apathy but to remind & expand others that we can all come to a place of self-empowerment.
Art by the amazing @daniellenoel.art (creator of Star & Moon Child Tarot)

Venus enters Aquarius ‚ôíÔ∏è Yay! Did you know that beyond relationship, material stability and inner values/self-worth‚Ä¶ Venus also reflects to us how we see/find beauty in the world. And that is why I love when she comes around to Aquarius - because here she is teaching us to find beauty in all things that are unusual, weird, different and very abstract. Aquarius, ruled by Uranus, is the archetype of evolution (I‚Äôm not saying that Aquarius‚Äôs are the most evolved - we all have this energy inside of ourselves).. but Venus here is supporting us to radically evolve the way we relate to one another and shifts our perception of what a relationship should look like. Aquarius helps to take us far outside of the box. Channeling the future into the present. On a self-worth level - Venus in Aquarius fulfils itself through having values that rebel against the norm of society‚Ä¶ and feels good when it is different and doing the unexpected. Venus in Aquarius comes to teach us that we can find expansive connection with unexpected mates. She teaches us how to find new levels of freedom in the realm of love. And switches up our relationship to the material realm & money. Changing our understanding of what value even is in the first place? Such a subjective thing hey? We all value the same thing differently depending on what it will give us. Makes us question how we price certain items the same even though they offer differing value to different people‚Ä¶ anyways‚Ä¶ queue calling in my alien lover. Blast off x
By one of my new fav collage artists: @sistersofthethers üå∏

Moon-Chiron Initiation üíî
As the moon dances through Libra we are asked to invite more harmony into our relationships and beauty into our lives. Libra finds peace through balancing its environment which can even manifest through aesthetic beauty and balancing it‚Äôs relationships, learning how to have an equal give-and-take. For those of you that struggle seeing the other persons perspective, this moon in Libra supports you to feel into the other persons perspective and emotional process. The moon in Libra reminds me of soft clouds, gentle kisses and french sweeties. You can tell that there is such a lightness to the Libran energy and its purity - maybe we need this at the moment since we‚Äôve been doing such deep work with the Capricorn stellium. Every month for the next 7 years we are going through an initiation as the moon in Libra comes to oppose Chiron in Aries. This opposition activates a core wounding around personal identity - coming back to that balance between self and the other. We may find this wounding reflected back to us through our external relationships. How we have not been fully honouring ourselves. Where we struggle to be assertive, independent and set healthy boundaries. Those are some Aries major lessons - along with moral outrage. Chiron is the wounded healer - to heal we must first become aware of and process our wound - and this Moon-Chiron opposition helps us recognise where we‚Äôve been storing energetic blockages in the body... probably why I had no energy yesterday!  because my body was energetically processing and this transit lands close to my nodal axis. What is your core wounding that continues to surface time and time again? 
Photographer: @matialonsor üíû

üå∏ Mars sextile Saturn üå∏
Mars in penetrating Scorpio is holding hands with disciplined Saturn in Capricorn. This planetary relationship support us in reeling it in and getting some hard work done. Those born with this aspect are a force to be reckoned with when it comes to dedication, discipline and commitment to their field of choice. Mars in Scorpio has potential for obsessive tendencies - becoming overly zoned in on one thing and forgetting to share a light-hearted space with the people around you. This combo can cause us to be harsh, overly intense and blunt. Certain resentments may surface to be dealt with. Some of us may even feel that we have pent up energy but an inability to channel it in a healthy way. Think of a container that keeps building with pressure but has no release. It suddenly bursts! Therefore, jump the gun and start attending to the smallest frustrations in a healthy way. Once Mars moves around to sextile Pluto (in the next week) certain obsessions and impulsive desires may intensify‚Ä¶ Feeling overcome with primal desires beyond our rational control. Don‚Äôt surround yourself with people who rub you up the wrong way because the situation is unlikely to end well. On the other hand, channel your energy into deep intimacy and passionate sex. Mars in Scorpio finds sexual healing and Pluto takes us to those places that are cathartic but generally avoided. Put on the detective glasses for self-exploration and ‚Äòinto-me-i-see‚Äô.

üåë Eclipse Season üåë
The Universe uses Eclipses as a way to wake & shake us up to things that need to change in our lives. That is why certain things feel as though they are happening outside of our control - even though deep down we‚Äôve known that the situation wasn‚Äôt in alignment with our highest truth. The Eclipses will clear out anything that has been blocking what you‚Äôve been consciously or unconsciously calling into your life. They will bring awareness to some of life‚Äôs greatest and most unexpected events. Eclipses bring us to points in our lives that we can never turn back again. And this is truly for our greatest good as souls on an evolutionary journey. The Eclipses want us to see the truth - within ourselves, the situation and most likely in the people around us! Get brutally honest. Before these upcoming Eclipses on the 26th of December (4 degrees Capricorn) & 11th of January (20 degrees Cancer) - I recommend getting clear on what you‚Äôve been calling into your life and what is potentially blocking that from coming through. Don‚Äôt take any messages/signs/insights around the Eclipses lightly. Implement them and know that by doing so you will live a more fulfilling and honest life moving forward. We don‚Äôt know what to expect around these times - some of you won‚Äôt feel anything at all but some might feel rattled to the core. Try to avoid putting labels on these experiences & don‚Äôt act too quickly. Surrender to certain events unfolding - allow the dust to settle and time to integrate. You may be gifted the opportunity to have a whole new experience of life that you never thought possible. 
Art by @starkissedkate üåå

üå± Earth Moon üå±
As the Moon enters Virgo later today and begins to trine the incredible stellium (multiple planets) in Capricorn‚Ä¶ we must be aware of how much responsibility we are taking on. How much pressure are you putting on yourself? Where are you feeding unnecessary anxiety and worry? The Moon in Virgo/Capricorn Stellium is very good at putting a way too heavy workload on its shoulders. And around this time of year we must all remember to take a breather. It is important to remind this nervous prone Virgo Moon that it doesn‚Äôt have to do everything on its own - you can delegate to the people around you and also to the universe. Remembering that without being in control of every detail certain things will still fall into place as they are meant to. Know when the time is right to surrender to what is. No kind of stress is worth your health and wellbeing. I know it‚Äôs easier said than done (Virgo)‚Ä¶ but that is where you have to start putting yourself first, filling up your cup before you can be in service to the people around you. Alternatively, for those that struggle to be disciplined and get shit done. Harness this energy to create some structure & organisation for this holiday season. Feeling a bit heavy? Dense? Stuck? Why don‚Äôt you try cleaning. Therapy for Moon in Virgo is cleaning it‚Äôs environment, body & mind. Material things hold energetic value - maybe its time to get rid of whatever no longer aligns with you - creating some energetic space for the new year.... and Christmas gifts üå∑
Artist: unknown (?)

üå∏ Worthiness üå∏
If I can give you one practical piece of advice leading up to this Eclipse - How are you placing your worth outside of yourself? What are you basing your worth on externally? By doing this we are literally putting our power outside of ourselves and basing it on something that is an illusion. We are literally disempowering ourselves. The thing is that we have been so deeply conditioned to do this - we are all buying into the illusion. Everything external to you dissolves with time - whereas what you hold within will continue to grow and blossom if you choose to water it. Beauty truly comes from within. The longer you gain validation from that which is outside of you - the further you move away from your truth & the further you move away from a true sense of happiness. What can you do today to bring your power back to yourself? Comment below where you‚Äôve been placing your worth externally - vulnerability is appreciated as we support one another to see that you are not alone. Let‚Äôs help to wake each other up. And bring awareness to all of the unique gifts that you hold within you. Reframe the game. Start valuing yourself from within. This is true power. 
Art by @lost_in_time_designs

üì° Happy Lunation Station 
Is your soul fragmented? How do you lack integration of expression in your interactions? In other words - do different situations make you step into different roles that take you far away from your true self. Or do you stay in your centre adapting slightly to the different interactions. A sweet little message about the energetic dynamics of this full moon... it is playing out on the Gemini (Moon) - Sagittarius (Sun) axis and is making a T-Square to Neptune in Pisces! Be more aware of the words that leave your mouth and have a committed intention to tell the truth. This energy can be blurry, confusing, foggy... sometimes our expression doesn‚Äôt match our intention. So before you act and express - get clear on your core intentions. Neptune is the window out into the ether. What lies inbetween is the fog of the ego. Fog that makes us question our authentic expression. Fog that confuses our desires and stumps integrity.  Fog that is consumed with fantasy, imagination and escapism. Inhibiting us from seeing the truth for what it really easy. We all know Gemini is mutable AF... sometimes mutating so quickly it doesn‚Äôt even know what is up or down, right or wrong. We need some serious grounding and integrity during this Full Moon! Positively, we are able to open our channels to the divine. Emotions, intellect and spirit aligned. Intention as the anchor for what will be received. Nothing wrong with a healthy decision to tap out of this reality for a moment. Just as long as you aren‚Äôt running away from anything. Neptune reminds me of listening to the inside of a sea shell and wondering what is on the other side üêö

üåï Full Moon in Gemini üåï
Hello lunar lovers! Comment ca va? The moon is full tomorrow at 19 degrees of Gemini. The sun is illuminating the wholeness of la luna by opposing her. The sun shines his light upon the most hidden and subconscious parts of self - making the Full Moon a somewhat emotional time. Those that are hyper sensitive to the movement of the moon were once called lunatic (pronounced loo-nahtic)- now known as lunatics. It‚Äôs well known that the collective energy heightens around the Full Moon! Luckily this Moon in Gemini brings a lighter energy with it - however, there is potential for our emotions and intellect to overwhelm us - making us feel like we are going a bit cray. Might need to take some adaptogens, CBD or whatever else helps to relax you during this lunation phase. Gemini is very good at activating the mind - enhancing our ability to communicate our emotional processes. There is a risk of becoming so intellectually active you disconnect from the heart completely. It is likely we will be having an active dreamtime - if you can manage to sleep. This Full Moon brings our attention to the duality in our lives, which is an illusion after all. How are you balancing the multiple areas of life? How does your desire for something different or the ‚Äògreener grass‚Äô rob you from enjoying the present moment. Be grateful for what is. Gemini is keen to have a taste of everything - sometimes lacking the ability to go deep into one thing. There is indeed potential for emotional overwhelm. We utilise the element of earth to counteract over-active yang energy. Coming back into the body, self-care practices and a pinch of routine. This is a social Full Moon where we might find ourselves giving birth to exciting new ideas & a more detached understanding of our emotions. Just be careful that a sense of boredom and indecisiveness doesn‚Äôt begin to affect the people around you. Not everyone is as mutable as you Gemini folk! Maybe you can support some of us to understand living a life of dual desires and emotions? An opportunity for us to experience polarities?
Art by: @zeewipark

‚ôêÔ∏è Mercury in Sagittarius ‚ôêÔ∏è Mercury the winged messenger has entered the archetype of Sagittarius yesterday evening. Mercury governs our intellect in the way we perceive and receive the world around us - Sagittarius as an archetype is adventurous, spontaneous and truth seeking. During this transit over the next 2.5 weeks we will be called into expansive, global truth so that we can find our own sense of faith. We have to be careful to not become overly tired up in our own personal truth and become dogmatic in our interactions with others. Sagittarius can sometimes be very blunt and abrupt in its delivery because it fails to see the truth outside of itself. Even though we are on a quest to find what is ours, we want to keep our mind open to allowing others to be just as they are. Mercury in Sagittarius wants to activate the right side of the brain - exploring philosophy, universal truths, religion and different cultural backgrounds... maybe this is a good time to pick up a new language or go and learn about a different culture than your own. 
Art: Leonardo da Vinci - ‚ÄúSalvator Mundi‚Äù circa 1500

For the babes & moments being born during this time... We have a lot of Capricorn heavy energy in the cosmos. Jupiter, Ceres, South Node, Venus, Saturn & Pluto all in Capricorn! Every moment of this day has a birth chart, every new child born has a birth chart, the momentary meeting with a new person has a birth chart - and if it has happened this year it is reflected by this major stellium. What does it mean? It means that the birth charts of these people, situations, entities carry a lot of duty, heaviness and responsibility with them. Although there is commitment, determination and ambition at the heart of the chart‚Ä¶ there is potential to be carrying too much pressure, density and even pain. Being overly hard on oneself - coming from a past life that involved a lot of self-sustaining behaviour and an inability to shift into the softness of the emotional realm. These children come in feeling as though they are foreign to the comfort and potential nurturing of family. They found their safety through being their own rock of support, out in the big wide world. The North Node in Cancer is calling these babes back into the heart, back into the feminine, back into balance with a maternal approach to life. Meaning that they are learning to find value in the realm of emotion again even if it doesn‚Äôt have a practical result in this material realm. They are learning the power of vulnerability, sensitivity and softness - seeing this as a strength rather than a weakness. Collectively, all of the heaviness & conditioning of the past is being brought to a head so that it can finally melt away (if you allow it so). We are being asked to recondition what success means to us. Break free of the shackles you have placed on yourself - they don‚Äôt actually belong to you anyways! They belong to the society you grew up in, the authority systems you were surrounded by and other unconscious behaviours you were exposed to as a young babe. These magnificent beings come in as wonderful space holders but are learning the art of allowing themselves to also be held during the process. Swipe for a real life pic of a Capricorn SN babe üåô open yourself to the sparkles of life ‚ú®

üåô Moon Musings üåô
The Moon in impulsive and passionate Aries is currently squaring Pluto & Saturn in disciplined Capricorn. Fiya fiyaaa üî• some potential for tension, conflict and friction indeed. As these two intense energies come to a head. The Saturn square can indicate feeling some emotional suppression and blockages. Emotional density may be at its fore... where the reality of a situation is hitting you smack bang in the face. That‚Äôs good! Saturn says there‚Äôs no time for fluffing about. Especially in the lead up to this Capricorn eclipse on the 26th of December. Pluto is also bringing to the fore some potentially painful emotional truths... again, nothing to fear here! Anywhere we‚Äôve been disillusioned or lying to ourselves is keeping us from our most authentic expression and greatest potential. Pluto square the Moon can bring about some obsessive feelings/thoughts... be careful to not get sucked too deeply into an emotional space that isn‚Äôt truly serving you. Recognise when it‚Äôs time to stop feeding certain emotional processes and just let them go for good. This transit is brief only lasting a couple of days üíò make the most of it üå™
Art by @hheininge

üåº Celestial Musings üåº
The Sun is halfway through his journey in adventurous Sagittarius. What are you taking from this transit? How are you harnessing the confident, spontaneous, freedom oriented Sag archetype? Have you felt more called towards individuation? Freedom of choice and movement? Seeking the truth - your truth. Sagittarius seeks truth so that it can anchor more expansively into FAITH. To have faith in life, in itself and the universe. How are you able to harness faith for the rest of this transit? And get clear on what your personal truth looks like. Just as long as it isn‚Äôt isolating you from connecting with others truths. The Moon is in Aries today making a neat conjunction to Chiron‚Ä¶ there is more fire in the air. Opportunity to heal some suppressed identity wounds. Two celestial bodies are supporting one another to assert oneself and be independent. Over the next couple of days give the people around you space to explore themselves and be whoever they need to be. We are all on a journey towards self discovery and reconditioning/rewiring‚Ä¶ maybe over these next couple of days this will be amplified. Meaning that we feel a bit more reactive/impulsive when dealing with certain situations. Frustration might build into explosive anger. Slow down - take time for yourself if you need to. Be fearless in the pursuit to reclaim yourself.

üßöüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Moon trine Mars üßöüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
As the Moon shifts through boundary-less Pisces and makes a flowing trine to penetrating Scorpio in Mars‚Ä¶ we are being urged to go within, transmute & transform so that we can be a clearer channel to connect with the divine. The Moon in Pisces tends to be like a sponge - highly sensitive to the energetics playing out around it. Thus, we must be aware that today we may not be as grounded as usual - feeling slightly in-between worlds. This Piscean Moon also invites us into fantasy and romanticism - looking at the world around us through a romantic lens. Take moments to tap out of earth realm and enter into creative flow. Better that we surrender to the present energies rather than fight against them. Once we surrender you never know what channeling might come through. Be aware if you are carrying somebody else‚Äôs burdens‚Ä¶ and know that many insecurities/worries we have do not even belong to us. This moon heightens our desire to escape‚Ä¶ and that Mars in Scorpio tends to enjoy finding the ‚Äòpeek‚Äô experience.. ego annihilating experiences. Be careful to not push yourself over the edge. Question your intentions before going deeper into something. Call on Pisces empathic abilities to understand and forgive.

‚ôëÔ∏è Jupiter trine Uranus ‚ôëÔ∏è Jupiter finally made his way into Capricorn today! Refer to my post a few days ago to dive deeper into what this means. Essentially, I almost see this transit as a somewhat friendly version of Saturn return - in the sense that we are still being called into maturity, responsibility and accountability - depending on what house this transit is passing through in your birth chart. Jupiter magnifies anything he touches - whether it goes in a good or bad direction. Meaning that we are still yet to be confronted by Capricorns harsh realism - no more escaping, pretending and fluffing around. Time to get to work! This transit is an exciting opportunity for us to all grow the fuck up! To creates some stable and long-lasting, healthy foundations for ourselves, families and the community. To action more discipline in our lives. Just as long as we don‚Äôt become overly ambitious, greedy and success driven. Over the couple of weeks this trine to Uranus in Taurus gives us a beautiful opportunity to reflect on our relationship to the material world. How do you self-sustain? Uranus in Taurus is re-conditioning what survival means to us. And re-conditioning the ways that we sustain ourselves in relationship to food/agriculture, money, beauty, material belongings - bringing it all back down to EARTH. Cue, natural beauty in all its forms. This earthy sextile to Jupiter facilitates us in establishing sustainable foundations for ourselves and Mother Earth. An expansive energy holding hands with a revolutionary energy - the capacity to bring about great change! Keep your eyes peeled for what is happening in your personal life and the collective over the next couple of weeks.

‚ôëÔ∏è Jupiter enters Capricorn ‚ôëÔ∏è ... on the 3rd of December. Jupiter, the planet of expansion and magnetism is entering the contrasting archetype of Capricorn (ruled by Saturn). Saturn & Capricorn have more suppressed, confining, disciplined nature - whereas Jupiter is everything but that. However, bring the two together and we might be able to find a way to channel some incredibly expansive energy down into this material plain. Jupiter will be in Capricorn for the next year - therefore, it is important to check which house he will be transiting in your birth chart! As you might find some beautiful support to ground some exciting ideas into manifestation. With Jupiter in Capricorn - your manifestations are totally possible and tangible - only if you are willing to take full responsibility and accountability of your present reality and anything blocking you from calling your manifestations in. Manifestation here literally equates to the amount of self-reflection & growth you are willing to do. We also must remain in integrity - aligning our words with our actions. Capricorn helps to hone the somewhat extremist energy of Jupiter in by reminding us to use discipline & determination to achieve our goals. The beauty of this transit is that it will call more stability & grounding into our lives. And the opportunity to create a healthy foundation for ourselves. Jupiters expansion is neutral - meaning that it can expand in a positive or negative direction. So on the other hand - we must be careful to not become overly hard on ourselves and the people around us, giving ourselves too much responsibility. Becoming overly materialistic and attached to reputation & success. With Jupiter in Capricorn we are truly creating value for the long-term in our lives. Be careful to also not PHYSICALLY over work yourself - health issues with Jupiter are related to extremism and Capricorn rules the bone structure in the body. Find a healthy balance between action and receptivity. And enjoy the fruits of your labor üçá
Artist: Emile Vernet Le Comte

‚ôëÔ∏è Venus enters Capricorn ‚ôëÔ∏è Venus is currently blazing a trail, swiftly giving us a taste of different archetypes. And yesterday already moved into Capricorn!
